# Vendor-specific AI infrastructure — personal / per-machine runtime state.
#
# IMPORTANT: this repo deliberately tracks AI *steering* files — CLAUDE.md,
# GEMINI.md, AGENTS.md, .cursorrules, .windsurfrules,
# .github/copilot-instructions.md — and the templates/ that ship them. Those are
# the product and must stay tracked. Only the personal runtime/IDE directories and
# local history/caches below are ignored (the "infrastructure", not the steering).
#
# The shared skills layer (agent-skills/) is likewise TRACKED. The runtime dirs below
# also hold local, regenerated skill *adapters* (.claude/skills/, .gemini/commands/,
# .cursor/rules/, .kiro/skills/, .github/skills/) — local-only; the neutral agent-skills/
# is the shared source of truth. (GitHub Copilot's adapter lives at .github/skills/, ignored
# path-scoped below — .github/ itself stays tracked for copilot-instructions.md + workflows/.)

# Agent / AI-IDE runtime directories
.kiro/
.claude/
.cursor/
.continue/
.windsurf/
.codeium/
.gemini/
.github/skills/
.cline/
.roo/
.zed/
.codex/

# Aider local history / cache (steering files like .aider.conf.yml stay tracked)
.aider.chat.history.md
.aider.input.history
.aider.tags.cache*

# OS / editor noise
.DS_Store

# Python bytecode cache — the bundled memory-lint helper script generates this on run;
# it is a build artifact, never committed (the .py source under agent-skills/ stays tracked).
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]

# Fresh-context review scratch (second-opinion / apply-critique skills) — personal,
# per-machine snapshots & critiques; sharing one is a conscious human decision, never committed.
review-scratch/
